<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-215] bad assert() in Monitor.cpp</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-215</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On certain kernels, waiting with a very long timeout (e.g. many minutes or hours) returns just before the expected time, hitting the assert and abruptly bringing down the whole process.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t have enough information about affected platforms to style an ifdef &amp;#8211; feel free to buttress the attached patch if you&apos;d prefer it to be more specific.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also attached for your consideration is a patch to compile thrift lib with -DNDEBUG.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Detected in linux 2.6.18-6&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
