                            <comment id="12651204" author="erikfrey" created="Thu, 27 Nov 2008 00:59:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Comments out the wait assert (with short explanation).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12652239" author="dreiss" created="Tue, 2 Dec 2008 02:17:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I found a few emails from our internal lists, and it looks like we&apos;ve seen this come up even with shorter timeouts.  I&apos;m about to commit the bad assert patch with a little change to the comment.  Do you really think it is necessary to compile with -DNDEBUG&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12652245" author="erikfrey" created="Tue, 2 Dec 2008 02:50:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I always thought compiling with -DNDEBUG was standard practice for release builds.  But it&apos;s not necessary within the scope of this bug.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
